<dl id="n30161c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n30" href="#n30161c">N30 (VI.B.22)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n30all.htm#n30161c"> 161(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">H</font> his skin roseose</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">We all know that <mark>the skin is flushed</mark> in sleep, noticeably so in children and in persons with transparent skins&mdash;hence, the &ldquo;sleeping beauty&rdquo;; but this means that if now the skin holds more blood, the brain is holding less. <small> D. F. Fraser-Harris, <a name="FHMS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FHMS"><cite title="source">Morpheus, or: The Future of Sleep</cite></a> (1928) 33</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
